<div class="grid-x">
            <div class="small-12 cell">

                <h4>Message from the Superintendent</h4>

                <p>Hello Hansen SD #415, Parents, Students, Patrons, and Staff:</p>

                <p>As many of you have heard, the Idaho State Board of Education voted to extend the soft closure of Idaho schools through the rest of the year with the caveat that a local board could decide to reopen if social distancing requirements are lifted and state-wide criteria are met (criterion will be developed over the coming week and any decision to reopen would be done in coordination with the local health department). This decision effectively extends the soft closure here in Hansen for the remainder of  the 19-20 school year. For now, I encourage all staff, students, and families to plan as if distance learning will continue for the remainder of the year.
                </p>

                <p>Our administrators will be working with teachers to identify and communicate the vital things we need students to master to close out the year. Our staff has appreciated all the support the families of our students have given to assist in their children(s) education during this unprecedented time. Let's continue to work together to make the next couple of months the best they can be!
                </p>

                <p>As the situation with COVID-19 changes so rapidly, please know our intent will be to do everything we can for our seniors and their graduation. We will continue to provide district updates as the weeks progress.
                </p>

                <p>Sincerely,<br>

                David Carson<br>
                    Superintendent Hansen School District #415</p>




            </div>
        </div>

